GAP 1: restartJob - No bounds checking on task index access
================================================================

Go allows direct array access without bounds checking:
  t := j.Tasks[j.Position-1]

If Position is 0 or > len(Tasks), Go will panic.
Rust has explicit bounds checking:
  if task_index >= job.tasks.len() {
      return Err(HandlerError::Handler(format!(
          "task index {task_index} out of range (job has {} tasks)",
          job.tasks.len()
      )));
  }

EXPECTED FIX in Go job.go restartJob():
Add bounds checking before accessing j.Tasks[j.Position-1], similar to Rust:
  position := j.Position
  if position < 1 || position > len(j.Tasks) {
      return errors.Errorf("task position %d out of range (job has %d tasks)", position, len(j.Tasks))
  }
  t := j.Tasks[position-1]

