GAP 8: restartJob - Go doesn't propagate task evaluation failure to job level
================================================================

In Go startJob (lines 83-89), when task evaluation fails, the job is marked as FAILED
via recursive handle call. But in Go restartJob, task evaluation failure does NOT
mark the job as FAILED - the job stays RUNNING with a FAILED task.

If this is intentional (to allow retry), document it. If not, add similar failure
propagation to restartJob:
  if t.State == tork.TaskStateFailed {
      return h.handle(ctx, job.StateChange, j)
  }

EXPECTED FIX (if intentional behavior change):
After task evaluation in restartJob, add:
  if t.State == tork.TaskStateFailed {
      j.FailedAt = &now
      j.State = tork.JobStateFailed
      j.Error = t.Error
      return h.handle(ctx, job.StateChange, j)
  }

